<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">There is a warlock talent that gives a short spirit boost after killing a mob. But you have to kill it with drain soul. If your group or even your pet gets the finishing blow (or maybe even a tick from other DoTs? I'm getting hazy on the details) you don't get it.
<br />

<br />
I found it was proccing about half of the time soloing if I went out of my way to try for it, and hardly ever while in a group. I dropped it when I respecced.
<br />

<br />
The priest talent at least works every time you kill something (at 5/5), and is very nice for soloing. But how often does a priest kill something in a group? If I play my priest alt enough I'm sure I'll drop this in a respec too.
<br />

<br />
Yes, they make spirit more useful than it would be otherwise. But it's still not much. Int/sta is the way to go for all casters as far as I can tell (hence the "who should roll on Dreadmist?" controversy).
<br />

<br />
I'd give at least even odds that will change in the future, but I'm not about to collect spirit gear in hopes that it happens.
<br />

<br />
Teremar Talfirien</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
